<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Carp2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Carp,</orth> vb., to cavil, to find fault, to mock: <cit><quote>such --ing is not commendable,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.1.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 1, 71</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ing fools,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.2.63" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 2, 63</bibl></cit> (Q<hi rend="sub">1</hi> <emph>capering</emph>). <cit><quote>envious --ing tongue,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.90" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 1, 90</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ing censures,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.5.68" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 5, 68</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>do hourly c. and quarrel,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.222" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 4, 222</bibl></cit>. -- Followed by <emph>at</emph>: <cit><quote>our motion will be mocked or --ed at,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.86" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 2, 86</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>